  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Bash the <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, slice down the middle lengthways, remove the tough outer layers (keep them for later!) and chop the <strong>softer inner stem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634572667227-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634572667227-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634572667227-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634572667227-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634572667227-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and 400ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat </p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>lemongrass rice</strong></p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634572670477-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634572670477-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634572670477-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634572670477-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634572670477-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Deseed the <strong>red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> pepper strips</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger </strong>and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>lemongrass</strong> and cook for 2-3 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1634572674622-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1634572674622-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1634572674622-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1634572674622-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1634572674622-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>basa fillets</strong> into pieces</p><p>Chop the <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and add the<strong> lime leaves</strong>, <strong>fish sauce</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
